                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W./10–1644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-16T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 16, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3947. I have received a letter from Vyshinski dated October 15 stating that the
                    Soviet Government has appointed Marshal of the Soviet Union F. I. Tolbukhin to
                    be Chairman of the Joint Allied Military Mission which will control the
                    withdrawal of Bulgarian troops from Greece and Yugoslavia. Colonel General S. S.
                    Biryuzov will be his deputy. Lieutenant General Cherepanov and Colonel Pleshkov
                    has [<hi rend="italic">have</hi>] been named assistants to the Chairman.</p>
                <p>This answers in part the questions raised in the Department’s 2431, October 14, 2
                    p.m., concerning the composition of the Soviet and British delegations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
